                            <comment id="13601018" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 13 Mar 2013 10:45:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test case and proposed fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13607464" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 10:05:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jukka addressed this issue in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-673&quot; title=&quot;Unified hook processing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-673&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-673&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a VisibleEditor wrapper.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13607466" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 20 Mar 2013 10:07:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added test in revision: 1458712&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13622485" author="anchela" created="Thu, 4 Apr 2013 16:34:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;while working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-709&quot; title=&quot;Consider moving permission evaluation to the node state level&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-709&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-709&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; i detected that we prevent hidden properties&lt;br/&gt;
to be exposed by the TreeImpl but we forgot to do the same for&lt;br/&gt;
hidden nodes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;adding such a restriction will cause this test case to fail.&lt;br/&gt;
IMO this test should rather operate on the node state level.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13623479" author="anchela" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 09:33:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-753&quot; title=&quot;TreeImpl exposes hidden child trees&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-753&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-753&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the corresponding issue for TreeImpl&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13623592" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 12:43:35 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;IMO this test should rather operate on the node state level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m attaching a test that only operates on node states. is this what you had in mind?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13623697" author="anchela" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2013 15:08:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes... thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13625206" author="mreutegg" created="Mon, 8 Apr 2013 07:20:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good. Applied patch in revision 1465547.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
